<br>
Dire charmed/thrall'd pets are really bad about ignoring the fact a mob has been mez'd and just smacking away.<br>
<br>
Our (necro) summoned pets aren't nearly as bad, but will sometimes (less than 5%) continue to attack and break a mez.<br>
<br>
Both charmed and summoned pets work correctly when unaggro'd and told to attack a mez'd mob. They give the correct message and refuse to engage.<br>
<br>
The biggest causes of broken mez’s are when pet is on Mob A, Mob B attacks owner, then Mob B is mez'd. Pet will finish the kill on Mob A, then if Mob B is nearby, turn around and punch Mob B in the face. Most of the time there's actually a few seconds pause, as if the pet is savoring the moment.<br>
<br>
Perhaps this isn't as noticeable to Mages as it is to Necros, due to the fact that many times we're the one casting the mez that Gabtik is joyously breaking.<br>
<br>
Two of the more informative threads we've had on it:<br>
