<br>
Sometimes it looks like a pet is still attacking a mezzed mob because when a pet first attacks something it usually takes a while for it to decide to face the direction of the mob it is attacking.  I have seen my pet attack a mob that it was facing the opposite direction of for a few seconds before it rotated and faced the mob it was attack numerous times.<br>
<br>
It is very unlikely that an epic pet will break a mez with its spell because it is instant cast.<br>
