<br>
Mez hits if pet is in mid swing, then your probably going to break mez.  Mez hits if your pet is in mid cast then your probably going to break mez.  <br>
<br>
You want a fix to mez?  /pet back off a few times til mobs are on the tank, /assist tank /pet attack, let chanter mez away.<br>
<br>
If pet is tank then chanter needs to mez a different mob, i.e. like one that the pet isn't attacking.  Alot of chanters I have seen throughout my EQ career have /assisted tank and mez'ed that mob more often than they should have.  Tanks often break mez's by haveing a DS on.  Mez hits, mob is in mid swing hit you and takes dmg from DS, mez breaks.  These are rare occurances, but people often blame tanks for being stupid and breaking mez's when it was the druid/mage that DS'ed them in reality.<br>
<br>
Fire pet is obviouse no no for places you &quot;might&quot; need to mez. AoE spells, how many times have I seen an AoE mez hit at the same time a wizzard or druid AoE'ed a rain.  I Personally only AoE when solo'ing, even then I prefer bolts.<br>
<br>
Pets and Mez'ed Mobs are as fix'ed as they are ever going to be, the one thing that would help, would be if the chanters thought to mez, other adds (the ones that the pet isn't on) first and let the pet take a few hits and stun the one the pet is on before mez'ing, to give you that window to get pet far away from mob before mez hits (only to show them, look my pet wasn't near it).  Really it wouldn't be a bad idea for chanters to stun all mobs before mez'ing them, for 2 reasons 1 to stop mob from swinging so it doesn't take DS dmg from finishing it's swing after mez hits. 2 to give a visual effect of which mob is to be mez'ed next and to give ALL melee/casters a few seconds to retarget the MA and /assist.<br>
<br>
As far as what my previouse post had to do with this topic?  Truthfully, not much towards the end, but I think I forgot to mention, /assist ma put me (and everyonelse that was with us) on the mob the chanter was trying to mez.  Sorry, it's not my job to select the target to attack, it's MA's job.  Notice the A it stands for /assist.  So in the begining it was on topic.   <br>
